sd=Customer Campaign Design	Design and refine customer campaign specifications based on their impact	A retention campaign is updated to provide amended/improved pricing terms that can be offered to targeted customers to help retain their business after a poor response rate has been detected for the campaign	This Service Domain designs and refines customer campaigns (or integrates designs from external campaign specialists). Customer campaigns target the existing customer base and can be proactive (involving customer targeting, contact and solicitation) or self-service and include activities such as cross-sell, up-sell and retention. Version numbering is used to track the impact of changes made to campaigns over their usage.
sdpath=customer-campaign-design
crpath=customer-campaign-specification
crr=Customer Campaign Specification Instance
mcr=Customer Campaign Specification
bqs=
CONFIG
CustomerCampaignSpecification	create	Create or register an imported customer campaign design		createCustomerCampaignSpecification		#desc
CustomerCampaignSpecification	update	Update details of a customer campaign specification or usage record		updateCustomerCampaignSpecification		#desc
CustomerCampaignSpecification	control	Control the use of a customer campaign specification (e.g. suspend pending revision)		controlCustomerCampaignSpecification		#desc
CustomerCampaignSpecification	exchange	Accept, reject, etc. a customer campaign specification		exchangeCustomerCampaignSpecification		#desc
CustomerCampaignSpecification	capture	Capture impact feedback against a customer campaign specification (by version number)		captureCustomerCampaignSpecification		#desc
CustomerCampaignSpecification	execute	Execute an automated action for a customer campaign specification (e.g. confirm eligibility requirements)		executeCustomerCampaignSpecification		#desc
CustomerCampaignSpecification	request	Request manual intervention with a customer campaign specification (e.g. obtain interpretation guidance)		requestCustomerCampaignSpecification		#desc
CustomerCampaignSpecification	retrieve	Retrieve details about a customer campaign specification (e.g. obtain use and impact reports)		retrieveCustomerCampaignSpecification		#desc
